modules.description: This module provides low-level runtime operations for interacting with the file system and executing external commands in a Unix environment using Eio. It supports operations like reading and writing files, checking file existence, creating directories, and running shell commands with customizable success checks. The module works directly with `Yocaml.Path.t` for path manipulation and handles errors through a dedicated error type.

This module provides functions to run and serve Yocaml programs in an Eio-based Unix environment, supporting dynamic site regeneration on file changes. It handles file system operations through the Runtime submodule, working with `Yocaml.Path.t` paths and custom error reporting via `custom_error_handler`. Concrete use cases include building and serving static websites with automatic rebuilds on source changes, using Eio for efficient I/O.
